# Daisy Patch SM ‚Äì Library Template & Reusability

## Language

- **All code, comments, and documentation must be in English.**
- Variable names, function names, class names, comments, Doxygen docs, and user-facing strings: English only.

## Template Structure (main entry point)

The main entry point (e.g. `MarkovChain.cpp`) follows a fixed pattern with **stub callback functions** that you implement:

```cpp
// Callbacks ‚Äì implement your logic here
void OnPotChanged(int index, float value) {
    switch (index) {
        case patch_sm::CV_1: /* Pot 1 */ break;
        case patch_sm::CV_2: /* Pot 2 */ break;
        case patch_sm::CV_3: /* Pot 3 */ break;
        case patch_sm::CV_4: /* Pot 4 */ break;
    }
}
void OnToggleChanged(bool toggleState) { /* ... */ }
void OnButtonPressed() { /* ... */ }

void UpdateValues() { /* ui.SetPotValue, ui.Update, set callbacks once */ }
void AudioCallback(...) { /* audio processing */ }
int main(void) { /* hw.Init, ui.Init, hw.StartAudio, main loop */ }
```

- **OnPotChanged**: `index` = CV_1..CV_4, `value` = mapped value [min..max]
- **OnToggleChanged**: `toggleState` = current toggle state
- **OnButtonPressed**: called on button rising edge

